        "inline_data": null,
        "text": "# \ud83d\udfe2 HEARTBEAT_WAKEUP\nYou have been routed ONE isolated task. \n*Task ID*: EPIC-DFP-MOD-ui-gateway\n*Module*: ui-gateway\n*Workdir*: /home/ienliven/Projects/sdlc-factory/workspace/EPIC-DFP-MOD-ui-gateway\n*Phase*: QA_REVIEW\n\n## SYSTEM CONTEXT\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"success\",\n  \"module_id\": \"ui-gateway\",\n  \"regression_context\": \"No active regression reported.\",\n  \"structural_context\": \"## > BEGIN_ENVIRONMENT\\n- **Stack**: Docker Compose (React/Vite/Nginx, Python/FastAPI, PostgreSQL)\\n- **Entry_Point**: `http://localhost:8000` (UI) and `http://localhost:8001` (API)\\n- **Interface_Mount_Selector**: `#root`\\n- **INTEGRATION_TEST_CMD**: `cd ui-gateway && CI=true npx playwright test --reporter=list`\\n## > END_ENVIRONMENT\\n\\n## > BEGIN_MODULE: ui-gateway\\n- **Type**: ORCHESTRATOR\\n- **Description**: The frontend application, Nginx reverse proxy, and global Docker Compose orchestrator.\\n- **Responsibilities**:\\n  - Write `docker-compose.yml` at the project root to orchestrate `ui-gateway`, `logic-api`, and `data-store`.\\n  - Map host port `8000` to container port `80` for the UI.\\n  - Map host port `8001` to container port `8001` for the API.\\n  - Configure Nginx to serve the React/Vite build and reverse proxy `/api/` to `http://logic-api:8001/api/`.\\n  - Implement the React UI with Tailwind CSS.\\n  - UI Components:\\n    - Header: \\\"Dimensional Factor Pulse\\\".\\n    - Heatmap: `@nivo/heatmap` or `apexcharts`. X-axis: Date, Y-axis: Funds. Diverging color scale. Tooltip with Date, Premium Value (4 decimal places), Region, Proxy Pair.\\n    - Controls: Fund Selector dropdown (US Core Equity, Intl. Vector, Emerging Markets, All), Timeframe Toggle (1D, 5D, 1M, 6M, 1Y, YTD).\\n    - Footer: \\\"Built by SDLC-Factory\\\" with `GIT_COMMIT_HASH` and `BUILD_DATE`.\\n  - E2E Testing: Playwright tests in `ui-gateway/tests/` to verify UI rendering and API integration.\\n- **Routing Contract**:\\n  - Nginx routes `^/api/(.*)$` to `http://logic-api:8001/api/$1`.\\n  - Docker Compose defines services: `ui-gateway` (builds from `./ui-gateway`), `logic-api` (builds from `./logic-api`), `data-store` (image `postgres:15-alpine`, uses `data-store/init.sql`).\\n## > END_MODULE: ui-gateway\",\n  \"semantic_context\": \"### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\\n\\n### File: test.py\\n```\\nhello factory\\n```\",\n  \"memory_insights\": \"No historic pgvector insights found for tester.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe SDLC Protocol and your Playbook are your core instructions.\nCRITICAL: If successful, your handoff JSON must strictly validate against this schema:\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\n    \"status\",\n    \"phase_completed\",\n    \"module_id\",\n    \"all_tests_passed\"\n  ],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"status\": {\n      \"const\": \"success\"\n    },\n    \"phase_completed\": {\n      \"const\": \"QA_REVIEW\"\n    },\n    \"module_id\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\"\n    },\n    \"all_tests_passed\": {\n      \"const\": true\n    },\n    \"failing_tests\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\nIf you learn an architecture-critical lesson, permanently save it for your future self using the native `sdlc_store_memory` tool.\n",
